race.description: Team Aidan Markets @ Crjc 23 November Mdn Plate
race.comment: STAR VENTURE (3) has had plenty of chances but looks ready to win. Took over a fair way from home and just failed to hang on last start over this distance at the Gold Coast. Cherry ripe at the third run back and won't get too many better chances to break through. ANOTHER CASHIE (6) is the obvious danger after an impressive debut over 1000m at Ballina last time, missing by a whisker after a fierce battle in the concluding stages. Wide gate the only reservation. NOADIAH (2) raced wide and lacked the kick required in a 1000m dash at this track first-up. Better placed out to this trip and the addition of blinkers might be a game changer. STRENUOUS (9) has not raced since finishing third to a G1 placegetter in Call Da Vinci at Ipswich in May. Trialled twice recently. Market watch advised. Pretty confident the winner comes from this quartet.
